h2 Prerecorded audio-only and video-only
div.chi-grid
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-breadcrumb
      ol.-text--normal
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="noopener" target="_blank") WCAG 2.2 Guideline
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#time-based-media" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 1.2 Time-based media
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#audio-only-and-video-only-prerecorded" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 1.2.1 Audio-only and Video-only (Prerecorded)
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .-lh--3
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs(data-tooltip="Content must be presentable to users in ways they can perceive." data-position="bottom")
        span Perceivable
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs.-ml--1(data-tooltip="Requirements must be satisfied to pass WCAG 2.2 Level A Success Criteria." data-position="bottom")
        span Level A
  .chi-col.-w--12
    p.-text
      | <strong>Benefits:</strong> Blind, deaf, cognitive/intellectual disabilities.
    p.-text
      | For prerecorded audio-only and prerecorded video-only media, the following are true, except when the audio or video is a media alternative for text and is clearly labeled as such:
    ul.-text
      li <strong>Prerecorded Audio-only:</strong> An alternative for time-based media is provided that presents equivalent information for prerecorded audio-only content.
      li <strong>Prerecorded Video-only:</strong> Either an alternative for time-based media or an audio track is provided that presents equivalent information for prerecorded video-only content.
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-card.-s--1.-rounded.-mb--3.-mt--1
      .chi-card__header
        .chi-card__title
          | How to pass
      .chi-card__content.-px--3
        ul.accessibility-checklist
          li 
            | Is information conveyed by prerecorded audio-only and prerecorded video-only content available to all users?  (Examples: Audio recording, text transcript, animation as a tutorial)
          li 
            | Can Assistive Technologies read text alternatives aloud, present then visually, or convert to braille for people who have difficulty perceiving visual content, or have difficulty understanding the meaning of prerecorded video content?
          li 
            | Can text be read for people who are deaf, are hard of hearing, or who are having trouble understanding audio information for any reason?

