        span Level A
  .chi-col.-w--12
    p.-text
      | <strong>Benefits:</strong> Blind and hard of hearing disabilities.
    p.-text
      | If any audio on a Web page plays automatically for more than 3 seconds, either a mechanism is available to pause or stop the audio, or a mechanism is available to control audio volume independently from the overall system volume level.
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-card.-s--1.-rounded.-mb--3.-mt--1
      .chi-card__header
        .chi-card__title
          | How to pass
      .chi-card__content.-px--3
        ul.accessibility-checklist
          li 
            | Can a sound that begins playing automatically on page load be stopped by the user via a control or link to turn the sound off?
            ul.-text
              li Is the control keyboard operable, located near the beginning of the page, and easily/quickly discovered by the user?
          li 
            | Can the screen reader user still hear the screen reader without other sounds playing/interfering?
          li
            | If a sound exists, does the sound play for 3 seconds or less, and stop automatically?
          li
            | Can a sound be played only on user request?

h2 Timing adjustable
div.chi-grid
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-breadcrumb
      ol.-text--normal
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="noopener" target="_blank") WCAG 2.2 Guideline
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#enough-time" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 2.2 Enough time
        li.chi-breadcrumb__item
          a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#timing-adjustable" rel="noopener" target="_blank") 2.2.1 Timing Adjustable
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .-lh--3
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs(data-tooltip="Users must be able to operate the interface." data-position="bottom")
        span Operable
      .chi-badge.-dark.-outline.-xs.-ml--1(data-tooltip="Requirements must be satisfied to pass WCAG 2.2 Level A Success Criteria." data-position="bottom")
        span Level A
  .chi-col.-w--12
    p.-text
      | <strong>Benefits:</strong> Blind, low vision, deaf, dexterity impairments, and cognitive limitations.
    p.-text
      | For each time limit that is set by the content, at least one of the following is true:
    ul.-text
      li <strong>Turn off:</strong> The user is allowed to turn off the time limit before encountering it; or
      li <strong>Adjust:</strong> The user is allowed to adjust the time limit before encountering it over a wide range that is at least ten times the length of the default setting; or
      li <strong>Extend:</strong> The user is warned before time expires and given at least 20 seconds to extend the time limit with a simple action (for example, "press the space bar"), and the user is allowed to extend the time limit at least ten times; or
      li <strong>Real-time Exception:</strong> The time limit is a required part of a real-time event (for example, an auction), and no alternative to the time limit is possible; or
      li <strong>Essential Exception:</strong> The time limit is essential and extending it would invalidate the activity; or
      li <strong>20 Hour Exception:</strong> The time limit is longer than 20 hours.
  .chi-col.-w--12
    .chi-card.-s--1.-rounded.-mb--3.-mt--1
      .chi-card__header
        .chi-card__title
          | How to pass
      .chi-card__content.-px--3
        ul.accessibility-checklist
          li 
            | Are users with disabilities given adequate time to interact with Web content?
          li 
            | Are options provided  to disable time limits, customize the length of time limits, or request more time before a time limit occurs, in order to helps those users who require more time than expected to successfully complete tasks?

